Styling-toggles-in-a-hierarchy","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can set a style for all toggle instances within a view hierarchy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by applying the style modifier to a container view. For example, you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can apply the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/button"},{"text":" style to an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack","type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["HStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $isFlagged) {","        Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","    }","    Toggle(isOn: $isMuted) {","        Label(\"Mute\", systemImage: \"speaker.slash.fill\")","    }","}",".toggleStyle(.button)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The example above has the following appearance when ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isFlagged"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isMuted"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Appearance","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS, iPadOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]]],"header":"row"},{"text":"Automatic styling","type":"heading","anchor":"Automatic-styling","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t set a style, OpenSwiftUI assumes a value of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/automatic"},{"text":", which corresponds to a context-specific","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default. Specify the automatic style explicitly to override a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"container’s style and revert to the default:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["HStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $isShuffling) {","        Label(\"Shuffle\", systemImage: \"shuffle\")","    }","    Toggle(isOn: $isRepeating) {","        Label(\"Repeat\", systemImage: \"repeat\")","    }","","    Divider()","","    Toggle(\"Enhance Sound\", isOn: $isEnhanced)","        .toggleStyle(.automatic) \/\/ Revert to the default style.","}",".toggleStyle(.button) \/\/ Use button style for toggles in the stack.",".labelStyle(.iconOnly) \/\/ Omit the title from any labels."],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The style that OpenSwiftUI uses as the default depends on both the platform","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and the context. In macOS, the default in most contexts is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ToggleStyle\/checkbox","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", while in iOS, the default toggle style is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Appearance","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Like toggle style does for toggles, the "},{"code":"View\/labelStyle(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifier sets the style for "},{"code":"Label","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instances in the hierarchy. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example above demostrates the compact "},{"code":"LabelStyle\/iconOnly","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" style,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which is useful for button toggles in space-constrained contexts."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Always include a descriptive title for better accessibility."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For more information about how OpenSwiftUI chooses a default toggle style,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"see the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ToggleStyle\/automatic","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" style.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/placeholdercontentview\/togglestyle(_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"title":"toggleStyle(_:)","role":"symbol","extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP0aB2UIE11toggleStyleyQrqd__AD06ToggleG0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore22PlaceholderContentViewV","remoteSource":{"fileName":"ToggleStyle.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/Toggle\/ToggleStyle.swift#L460"},"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"toggleStyle"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP0aB2UIE11toggleStyleyQrqd__AD06ToggleG0Rd__lFQO1Sqd__mfp","text":"